# nzfs

Author: Peter Eriksson <pen@lysator.liu.se>
Date:   2026-03-25


This is a patch for the OpenZFS 'zfs' command that adds a number of features:

General changes:

Being more verbose when doing stuff, displaying a progress indicator (either a spinning dial, or a counter).


"zfs clean" - new command

A variant of 'zfs destroy' that only works on snapshots, also adds support
for utilizing the additional features that is added to 'zfs snap', like being able
to select snapshots to delete based on age, or looking at a special "expires" propert,
or selecting snapshots using regexps. Also adds support for doing cleanups in parallell, or
limiting the number of snapshots deleted (batching)


"zfs snap" - more features

Being more verbose (if selected), being able to skip taking snapshots if no changes, or skipping
snapshots if there is too little space available, and being able to set an "expire" property on the
created snapshots.


"zfs upgrade -n" - added feature

Using "-n" the zfs upgrade command only prints the current ZFS filesystem version, and does not
loop over all filesystems checking for upgradable ones.
